<section class="domar_blog blog_v2 section_padding" style="padding:20px">
    <div class="container">
        <div style="margin: 5px">
            <h3 align="center">Causes of Loneliness</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="row align-items-center justify-content-around">
            <div class="col-lg-9 col-md-9 col-sm-9">
                <div style="text-align: center;margin-bottom: 0px;width: 100%;margin: 0 auto">
                    <p class="text-left">Loneliness is a universal phenomenon. It can happen to anyone, regardless of age, culture and race. Young adults, specifically during their transition to university, are highly susceptible to feeling lonely because they are faced with the stress of living away from their families and lacking the previous social from their usual friends (Rubenstein & Shaver, 1982). There are many reasons as to why these young university students feel lonely such as being rejected by others and feeling difficult to blend in. In one study, Japanese university students tend to feel lonely because they could not blend in, feeling out of place, and being rejected by others and on the other hand, Chinese university students tend to feel lonely when they are unable to find other people who share the same interests (Xie, Kawata, Kamimura, & Shibata, 2021).</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-3 col-sm-3">
                <div class="domar_img" style="float: none;display: block;margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;">
                    <img src="/assets/images/Causes.png" class="img-fluid" alt="">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>
</section>

