<section class="domar_blog blog_v2 section_padding" style="padding:20px">
    <div class="container">
        <div style="margin: 5px">
            <h3 align="center">Coping with Loneliness</h3>
        </div>
        <div style="text-align: center;margin-bottom: 0px;width: 70%;margin: 0 auto">
            <p>There are many ways that people react to loneliness. These are called coping strategies. Research (Rubenstein & Shaver, 1982) had shown that there are four main categories of coping strategies</p>
        </div>
        <div class="row justify-content-around" style="margin-top: 10px">
            <div class="col-lg-5 col-md-5 col-sm-12" style="float:left;border: solid 5px;border-color: green;border-radius: 25px;margin-bottom:25px">
                <div class="blog_box">
                    <div style="margin: 5px">
                        <h4 align="center">Social Contact</h4>
                    </div>
                    <div class="domar_img">
                        <img src="/assets/images/Social-Contact.jpg" class="img-fluid" alt="">
                    </div>
                    <div class="domar_info" style="text-align: justify;margin-bottom: 0px">
                        <p>
                            This type of coping strategy suggests people to try to call a friend, going to visit someone or trying to establish some kind of social contact when you have feelings of loneliness. The researchers thought that social contact may be a positive way of dealing with loneliness. People can go out and make some new friends who share the same interests. These can lead to a deeper relationship.
                            MeetPeeps provide the tool for you to join clubs and organization to make new connections.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-5 col-md-5 col-sm-12" style="float:left;border: solid 5px;border-color: green;border-radius: 25px;margin-bottom:25px">
                <div class="blog_box">
                    <div style="margin: 5px">
                        <h4 align="center">Active Solitude</h4>
                    </div>
                    <div class="domar_img">
                        <img src="/assets/images/ActiveSolitude.jpg" style="width: 100%;height: 100%" class="img-fluid" alt="">
                    </div>
                    <div class="domar_info" style="text-align: justify;margin-bottom: 0px">
                        <p>In this coping strategy, people tend to engage in their active behaviors by doing things that they like such as reading or writing. This is a positive and healthy coping strategy because it distracts the mind from loneliness and direct their energies towards doing something creative or productive.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-5 col-md-5 col-sm-12" style="float:left;border: solid 5px;border-color: green;border-radius: 25px;margin-bottom:25px">
                <div class="blog_box">
                    <div style="margin: 5px">
                        <h4 align="center">Spending Money</h4>
                    </div>
                    <div class="domar_img">
                        <img src="/assets/images/SpendingMoney.jpg" class="img-fluid" alt="">
                    </div>
                    <div class="domar_info" style="text-align: justify;margin-bottom: 0px">
                        <p>In this coping strategy, people meet new people by getting out of the house and spending their money. The researchers are neutral about this strategy because it can be both a good and bad way of coping with loneliness. When people spend money on things that they do not need or they overspend their money, this strategy can be very unhealthy. The researchers suggested to spend money on things that will cause you to be social with other people or just go out to the malls and look around without spending too much.</p>
                        <!--								<a href="#" class="btn_link">Read More</a>-->
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-5 col-md-5 col-sm-12" style="float:left;border: solid 5px;border-color: green;border-radius: 25px;margin-bottom:25px">
                <div class="blog_box">
                    <div style="margin: 5px">
                        <h4 align="center">Sad Passivity</h4>
                    </div>
                    <div class="domar_img">
                        <img src="/assets/images/SadPassivity.jpg" class="img-fluid" alt="">
                    </div>
                    <div class="domar_info" style="text-align: justify;margin-bottom: 0px">
                        <p>This coping strategy is the unhealthiest coping strategy. People that uses this strategy engages in activities that amplifies their loneliness instead of relieving it. Examples of the activities are watching TV, sleeping, eating, taking drugs, sitting and thinking and doing nothing. These activities only worsen the loneliness. You have to consciously decide to stop this sad passivity and move onto something more positive. Take it one step at a time, find a new hobby, go out and join a new club, pick up exercising, find something useful to do with your time, something that will make you a better person.</p>
                        <!--								<a href="#" class="btn_link">Read More</a>-->
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
